 ork
17.04.2017 19:19:51
Na tebe krásně sedí to, co řekl Sokrates.

"Misanthropy develops when without art one puts complete trust in somebody
thinking the man absolutely true and sound and reliable and then a little
later discovers him to be bad and unreliable ... and when it happens to
someone often ... he ends up ... hating everyone." Misanthropy, then, is
presented as a potential result of thwarted expectations or even excessively
na&#239;ve optimism, since Plato argues that "art" would have allowed the
potential misanthrope to recognize that the majority of men are to be found in
between good and evil.
